TITLE: Implementing Pub-Sub Pattern with PubSubRedisBroker
DESCRIPTION: Example usage of PubSubRedisBroker for implementing a publisher and subscriber using Redis. The publisher sends a message, and the subscriber listens for and logs the received message.
SOURCE: https://github.com/discordjs/discord.js/blob/main/packages/brokers/README.md#2025-04-16_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
// publisher.js
import { PubSubRedisBroker } from '@discordjs/brokers';
import Redis from 'ioredis';

const broker = new PubSubRedisBroker(new Redis());

await broker.publish('test', 'Hello World!');
await broker.destroy();

// subscriber.js
import { PubSubRedisBroker } from '@discordjs/brokers';
import Redis from 'ioredis';

const broker = new PubSubRedisBroker(new Redis());
broker.on('test', ({ data, ack }) => {
	console.log(data);
	void ack();
});

await broker.subscribe('subscribers', ['test']);
```

